Create a client-side executor that filters issues in memory using the parsed query AST.

## Requirements
- Take AST from query parser and array of issues
- Return filtered issues matching all criteria
- Support all operators defined in ADR-0023
- Optimize for performance (<50ms for 5,000 issues)
- Handle edge cases (null fields, type coercion)

## Implementation
```typescript
function executeClientQuery(
  query: SearchQuery, 
  issues: Issue[]
): Issue[] {
  return issues.filter(issue => 
    matchesQuery(issue, query)
  );
}

function matchesTerm(issue: Issue, term: SearchTerm): boolean {
  const value = getFieldValue(issue, term.field);
  switch (term.operator) {
    case 'gte': return value >= term.value;
    case 'contains': return String(value).includes(term.value);
    case 'regex': return term.value.test(String(value));
    // ...
  }
}
```

