Implement the hybrid search strategy that uses client-side cache for common queries and falls back to server for full-dataset searches.

## Requirements
- Define cache window (e.g., 2,000 most recent issues)
- Classify queries as cache-only, server-only, or hybrid
- Show UI indication when results may be incomplete
- Provide 'Search all' action for full-dataset queries

## Query Classification
```typescript
interface SearchStrategy {
  cacheOnly: string[];   // status, priority, type, assignee, sort
  serverOnly: string[];  // description (FTS), date ranges, regex
}

function classifyQuery(query: SearchQuery): 'cache' | 'server' | 'hybrid' {
  const fields = query.terms.map(t => t.field);
  if (fields.every(f => strategy.cacheOnly.includes(f))) {
    return 'cache';
  }
  if (fields.some(f => strategy.serverOnly.includes(f))) {
    return 'server';
  }
  return 'hybrid';
}
```

## UI Indication
When results may be incomplete, show:
'Showing X results from recent issues [Search all ‚Üí]'

